{
  "name": "RPlog_Tarroc_s_Dream",
  "title": "A Lesson by the Yavin Waterfall",
  "summary": "Falling asleep at his Corellia home, Tarroc finds himself in a vivid dream within a tropical rainforest, where a laughing eight-year-old girl chasing an iridescent insect leads him to a breathtaking waterfall. He slowly recognizes her as Jessalyn, who insists this is no mere dream but a vision within the Force, sharing her own childhood memories of Yavin where she first touched the Force. Speaking with the wisdom of a Jedi Master despite her childlike form, Jessalyn warns that the Jedi Master is missing and that she too will soon be gone, so Tarroc must learn to feel the Force on his own until he can find a teacher. She guides him to a starlit lake and a lotus blossom, showing him how to sense the living bond of the Force, and the dream shifts to a memory of him flying years ago, the moment he first felt it. Now appearing as the grown woman she is, Jessalyn embraces Tarroc in farewell, urging him to always feel the Force, and the two part with promises to meet again someday.",
